  "body": "<!-- This form is for bug reports and feature requests ONLY! \r\n\r\nIf you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\nBug Report\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nThis is related to https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/46806\r\nI am trying to integrate Cloud Foundry UAA (https://github.com/cloudfoundry/uaa) with kubernetes using the OIDC flow and the JWT  validation is failing on the kubernetes side with an error of email_verified is required.\r\n\r\n1.  email_verified is not a required claim in the OIDC core spec \r\n2.  From a security point of view email_verified is useful when Self Service is enabled which is true of internet identity providers\r\n3. Enterprise User Provisioning workflow in almost all cases is admin driven and not self service and email_verified becomes an obsolete claim. \r\n\r\nWith things as they stand today, this flow is not conducive to Enterprise Identity Providers.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nAuthentication should succeeed\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nPass a JWT which is missing email_verified claim using the OIDC flow into kubernetes\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\nClient Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"9\", GitVersion:\"v1.9.0\", GitCommit:\"925c127ec6b946659ad0fd596fa959be43f0cc05\", GitTreeState:\"clean\", BuildDate:\"2017-12-16T03:15:38Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.9.2\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"darwin/amd64\"}\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n\r\n@kubernetes/sig-auth-bugs",
